# 09.9 Best Practice

## Training Objective

To reinforce effective coordination techniques.

---

## Key Knowledge

- Efficient communication
- Predictability
- Professional discipline

---

## Operational Application

Controllers shall:

- Apply the “no surprises” principle
- Coordinate early and clearly
- Maintain predictable operations

---

## 1. Overview

Best practice ensures safe and efficient coordination between units.

---

## 2. Core Content

### 2.1 No Surprises Principle

- Aircraft shall be transferred in expected conditions

### 2.2 Stability

- Aircraft shall be stable before transfer

### 2.3 Clarity

- Communication shall be clear and unambiguous

---

## 3. Standards

- Controllers shall operate in a predictable and professional manner

---

## 4. Notes

- Good coordination reduces workload for all sectors
